  "Is it fast or slow?": "00b568b46512.mp3",
  "Deep or shallow?": "c67b00839987.mp3",
  "Don't change it, just notice.": "946b4c3cfab2.mp3",
  "Ocean waves have a pattern: they rise, they crest, they fall.": "c5e71eab0d61.mp3",
  "Your thoughts work the same way.": "43eee294c943.mp3",
  "When a thought comes, don't fight it.": "c1dc16922cab.mp3",
  "Watch it rise, crest, and dissolve, like a wave.": "eb322f23e428.mp3",
  "Now scan your shoulders, your jaw, your forehead.": "a17c4d1a3956.mp3",
  "These are where most people hold stress.": "1b4ddb2bfb1c.mp3",
  "Consciously release each one.": "04851054b711.mp3",
  "Drop your shoulders.": "9d0db88dca0e.mp3",
  "Unclench your jaw.": "a52a2be008bd.mp3",
  "Smooth your forehead.": "3911b719a658.mp3",
  "Here's something interesting: your brain can't tell the difference between vividly imagining calm and actually being calm.": "4fb2cf0c8e4a.mp3",
  "So right now, your brain genuinely thinks you're floating in the ocean.": "c9a2f42e10cf.mp3",
  "Take three final breaths.": "8f1b8c640cef.mp3",
  "With each one, say a word silently: Calm.": "30ea3ee0cca4.mp3",
  "Strong. Ready.": "aa54d36dc93b.mp3",
  "When you open your eyes, you'll carry this ocean calm with you.": "6cd3622ae15e.mp3",
  "Gently wiggle your fingers and toes.": "95b42e954426.mp3",
  "That body scan technique is a tool you can use anywhere — in your room, before a test, even on the bus.": "cc3800cf9e68.mp3",
  "Sit comfortably.": "215afdf2e6ff.mp3",
  "We're going to practice grounding — a technique that connects you to the present moment using your senses.": "d8933466c420.mp3",
  "Imagine you're in a quiet forest.": "7fba8a4f853e.mp3",
  "Start by noticing five things you can see in your mind's eye: the bark on trees, light through leaves, moss on rocks, a bird on a branch, a path ahead.": "cb00d5514cb2.mp3",
  "Now four things you might touch: rough bark under your hand, cool breeze on your skin, soft earth under your feet, a smooth pebble in your pocket.": "b9c9e1359bf6.mp3",
  "Three things you'd hear: birds calling, wind in the leaves, a distant stream.": "d6eaed617452.mp3",
  "Really hear them in your mind.": "f9ce0ff8b64e.mp3",
  "Two things you'd smell: fresh pine needles and damp earth after rain.": "4f2ce8448aba.mp3",
  "One thing you'd taste: clean, cool mountain air.": "992d3474ad4b.mp3",
  "This is called the 5-4-3-2-1 method.": "d044d8ffda19.mp3",
  "It works because anxiety lives in the future.": "fb70111dc4d5.mp3",
  "When you engage your senses, you pull your brain back to right now, where you're safe.": "2969289e813d.mp3",
  "Let's add breath to it.": "ff327f1b8727.mp3",
  "Breathe in for four counts...": "15bb3dc93a91.mp3",
  "out for four...": "11a1fd51d9df.mp3",
  "hold for four.": "03403d79e0d3.mp3",
  "This is box breathing — it balances your nervous system.": "20465a00068f.mp3",
  "Do two more rounds of box breathing.": "bf5d0f3d7532.mp3",
  "There's no rush.": "c7c122346484.mp3",
  "If your mind wanders, that's normal — just gently bring it back.": "7de95cb118f5.mp3",
  "That 'bringing back' is the exercise.": "95da8d3ce393.mp3",
  "Every time you do it, your focus gets stronger.": "6d2998229518.mp3",
  "Take one final deep breath.": "b7ae7ded5b9b.mp3",
  "Open your eyes slowly.": "4c2e2f16719f.mp3",
  "The 5-4-3-2-1 grounding method is yours now.": "62eb5b5d90c5.mp3",
  "Use it anytime you feel overwhelmed or scattered.": "99702d148a62.mp3",
  "Get comfortable.": "d5df123bcd37.mp3",
  "Today we're going to explore perspective — and there's no better place for that than space.": "571f12b358cc.mp3",
  "Begin with five slow breaths.": "b430b0703d3e.mp3",
  "In for four, out for six.": "2afc9bc5df55.mp3",
  "Each exhale slightly longer than the inhale.": "6ae8aae7b30d.mp3",
  "This tells your nervous system it's safe to relax.": "34120cfd3fe8.mp3",
  "Imagine you're rising above your room, above your building, above your neighborhood.": "8f5eb0d9b6e4.mp3",
  "You can see the whole town below, then the whole country.": "a2706a6636ed.mp3",
  "Keep rising.": "be36437c7048.mp3",
  "From up here, you can see the curve of the Earth.": "555a5bb30733.mp3",
  "The blue atmosphere, thin as an eggshell.": "99109b7a35d5.mp3",
  "All the people, all the drama, all the worries — they look so small from here.": "e6366f3cf9bf.mp3",
  "This is called cognitive distancing.": "75f33f9e13ed.mp3",
  "When you zoom out in your mind, problems feel more manageable.": "ab0f7fc4a116.mp3",
  "They're still real — but they're not the whole picture.": "b1af18a9bf96.mp3",
  "Now let's do a progressive relaxation.": "02f4726370b4.mp3",
  "Tense your feet for five seconds...": "d3a097ef02dc.mp3",
  "and release.": "15ea01c6f3c2.mp3",
  "Tense your legs...": "7b800b47cfcb.mp3",
  "Tense your belly...": "55e75a598d29.mp3",
  "Tense your hands into fists...": "ae642fba889d.mp3",
  "Scrunch your shoulders toward your ears...": "a0833abaa895.mp3",
  "and drop them.": "ee0c859e0240.mp3",
  "Scrunch your face tight...": "78ac9708b52c.mp3",
  "and let it melt away.": "49bf88b989c0.mp3",
  "Notice how different your body feels when tension is gone.": "134089abb507.mp3",
  "That heavy, warm feeling?": "2c70de46c4e7.mp3",
  "That's your parasympathetic nervous system — your body's built-in chill mode.": "74a3bfd67761.mp3",
  "From space, think about one thing you're grateful for today.": "43b2e025357d.mp3",
  "Research shows gratitude physically changes your brain, growing the areas that handle empathy and wellbeing.": "36b74e5c3a51.mp3",
  "Slowly drift back to Earth.": "da60300cbe40.mp3",
  "Feel your body in your seat.": "e420ad345204.mp3",
  "You just used perspective, progressive relaxation, and gratitude — three powerful mental health tools.": "aca156f8d14d.mp3",
  "Settle in somewhere comfortable.": "c6962074958b.mp3",
  "We're going to practice acceptance meditation using the metaphor of rain.": "6e164048844b.mp3",
  "Imagine sitting under a solid shelter while rain pours around you.": "706ba52f5b0a.mp3",
  "You're dry, safe, watching the rain.": "09a0ae2e6c62.mp3",
  "Start with deep belly breaths — feel your stomach expand as you inhale.": "695a6e5958b5.mp3",
  "The rain represents all the things you can't control: other people's opinions, unexpected changes, things that didn't go your way today.": "d9b477afe4e5.mp3",
  "Here's the key: you don't have to stop the rain.": "194bfc966d67.mp3",
  "You can't.": "bc943b72a8b4.mp3",
  "But you can choose to stay dry.": "095a9158f177.mp3",
  "Staying dry means not letting external things control how you feel inside.": "3e7cf072ac6d.mp3",
  "Notice any emotions you're feeling right now.": "a96a32df76ff.mp3",
  "Name them without judging: 'I notice I feel nervous.' 'I notice I feel tired.' Naming emotions reduces their power — scientists call this 'affect labeling.'": "57d33911334e.mp3",
  "The rain begins to ease.": "2601e775a0c1.mp3",
  "Each breath now is like pressing a reset button.": "452e3d32d2bf.mp3",
  "In: fresh energy.": "68eaed21f9c6.mp3",
  "Out: anything you don't need anymore.": "7c816602ad56.mp3",
  "Let's practice square breathing to deepen the calm.": "2be52e692647.mp3",
  "Inhale 4 counts...": "262d22a1c50b.mp3",
  "hold 4... exhale 4...": "f00adc578a25.mp3",
  "hold 4.": "f0cbe6c17979.mp3",
  "Imagine tracing a square with each breath.": "7fc46171bc10.mp3",
  "Fun fact: Navy SEALs use square breathing before high-pressure missions.": "fd6e1bcb7b10.mp3",
  "If it works for them, it definitely works for school, friendships, and everything else you navigate.": "fc233ac35ab4.mp3",
  "The rain stops.": "fdba3aa82fec.mp3",
  "Sunlight breaks through.": "85b2e61559a9.mp3",
  "A rainbow appears.": "46c21be74531.mp3",
  "Rainbows only happen because of the rain.": "33b3728f4ef6.mp3",
  "Some good things in your life also came from hard moments.": "77ff53f7a59c.mp3",
  "Open your eyes gently.": "4eed63db8e3b.mp3",
  "Today you practiced acceptance, affect labeling, and square breathing.": "0db7b0ee7441.mp3",
  "Three techniques backed by real science, available to you whenever you need them.": "15ab614e3b0f.mp3",
